title: SFH on human swine flu
content_text:
p>
Following is the transcript of remarks (English portion) made by the 
Secretary for Food and Health, Dr York Chow, at a media stand-up session 
after attending a public function today (December 10): Reporter: (on human swine flu) Secretary for Food and Health: I think there is a difference between the 
statistics of Hong Kong and the Mainland regarding the severity and 
particularly the mortality of pregnant women. We do not know exactly whether 
there are any additional factors that cause the high incidence of mortality,

there are any additional factors that cause the high incidence of mortality, 
although we know that pregnant women definitely carry higher risk. I don't 
know the exact treatment plan for those patients because in Hong Kong, we 
are fortunate that we have a very comprehensive testing kit that we can 
diagnose early. We can also have sufficient stock of anti-virals like 
Tamiflu and Relenza that we can apply early in the treatment of the disease. 
Although there are some doubts on whether Tamiflu is as effective as it

Although there are some doubts on whether Tamiflu is as effective as it 
claims, in the experience we have, particularly with the analysis of our 
laboratory as well as the laboratory of the Hong Kong University, it had 
shown that the viral load of patients that had received Tamiflu is much 
lower than those who had not received. In other words, it will definitely

lower than those who had not received. In other words, it will definitely control the severity and the mortality of patients. Reporter: Are there any plans for you to take human swine flu vaccination? Secretary for Food and Health: Yes, we did. We will tell you later. I definitely will be receiving the vaccination as one of the first individuals. (Please also refer to the Chinese portion of the transcript)
